    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_currency:
      description: Main currency of key figures, if not stated otherwise.
      example:
        isoCode: isoCode
        id: 4.078845849666752
      properties:
        id:
          description: Identifier of the currency. See endpoint `/basic/valueUnit/currency/main/list`
            for possible values.
          format: id32
          type: number
          x-positive: true
        isoCode:
          description: ISO 4217 code of the currency.
          type: string
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - id
      - isoCode
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_bonusYield:
      description: Bonus yield. It represents the bonus level adjusted for the cover
        ratio and currency cross rate minus the ask price of the securitized derivative.
        The value can become negative (e.g. for uncapped products), which does not
        mean that the investor will necessarily suffer a loss buying it. This key
        figure is calculated for bonus certificates with an intact knock-in barrier
        only, i.e. the attribute `knockIn.breach.breached` is false.
      example:
        annualized: 4.258773108174356
        absolute: 0.2025324113236393
        relative: 6.628464275087742
      properties:
        absolute:
          description: Bonus yield in absolute terms.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        relative:
          description: Bonus yield relative to the ask price.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        annualized:
          description: Annualized bonus yield relative to the ask price.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - absolute
      - relative
      - annualized
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_sidewaysYield:
      description: Sideways yield. It represents a hypothetical payout at maturity
        minus the ask price of the securitized derivative, under the assumption that
        all payout-influencing factors remain unchanged until maturity.
      example:
        annualized: 7.260521264802104
        absolute: 1.041444916118296
        relative: 4.678947989005849
      properties:
        absolute:
          description: Sideways yield in absolute terms.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        relative:
          description: Sideways yield relative to the ask price.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        annualized:
          description: Annualized sideways yield relative to the ask price.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - absolute
      - relative
      - annualized
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_maximumYield:
      description: Maximum yield. It represents a hypothetical maximum payout at maturity
        minus the ask price of the derivative. This key figure represents a theoretically
        possible best-case scenario, disregarding the probability of occurrence. It
        is calculated only for securitized derivatives with a limited payout (e.g.
        capped products).
      example:
        annualized: 9.702963800023566
        absolute: 9.132027271330688
        relative: 0.8774076871421566
      properties:
        absolute:
          description: Maximum yield in absolute terms.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        relative:
          description: Maximum yield relative to the ask price.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        annualized:
          description: Annualized maximum yield relative to the ask price.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - absolute
      - relative
      - annualized
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_agio:
      description: Agio. For plain vanilla warrants, it represents the difference
        between the ask price of the derivative and its parity (see attribute `parity`).
        Thus, for those with exercise right `call`, the agio indicates how much more
        expensive would it be to obtain the underlying through purchasing and exercising
        the warrant compared to directly purchasing the underlying. For those with
        exercise right `put`, the above consideration is applied inversely. For other
        types of securitized derivatives, the calculation and interpretation of the
        agio depends on their category. Negative values are possible.
      example:
        annualized: 5.507386964179881
        absolute: 0.5199002018724985
        relative: 7.933506881737151
      properties:
        absolute:
          description: Agio in absolute terms.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        relative:
          description: Agio relative to the underlying level.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        annualized:
          description: Annualized agio relative to the underlying level.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - absolute
      - relative
      - annualized
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_discount:
      description: Discount. It represents the difference between the ask price of
        the securitized derivative and the underlying level, adjusted for the cover
        ratio and the currency cross rate. This key figure is calculated only for
        discount certificates. For the value unit, see attribute `instrument.underlying.valueUnit.`
      example:
        absolute: 4.86315908102884
        relative: 6.073898085781152
      properties:
        absolute:
          description: Discount in absolute terms.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        relative:
          description: Discount relative to the underlying level.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - absolute
      - relative
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_breakEven_distance:
      description: Distance from the underlying level to the break even point.
      example:
        absolute: 4.459605034958679
        relative: 3.901545264248647
      properties:
        absolute:
          description: Distance in absolute terms. For the value unit, see attribute
            `instrument.underlying.valueUnit`.
          format: real
          type: number
        relative:
          description: Distance relative to the underlying level.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - absolute
      - relative
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_breakEven:
      description: Break even point. It represents the underlying level that has to
        be reached at maturity, such that no loss or profit occurs for the holder
        of the securitized derivative.
      example:
        distance:
          absolute: 4.459605034958679
          relative: 3.901545264248647
        breakEvenPoint: 8.251625748923757
      properties:
        breakEvenPoint:
          description: Break even point. For the value unit, see attribute `instrument.underlying.valueUnit`.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        distance:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_breakEven_distance'
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - breakEvenPoint
      - distance
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_spread:
      description: Spread of the securitized derivative. It represents the difference
        between the ask and bid price.
      example:
        harmonized: 0.43431398824148815
        relative: 2.9409642974827896
      properties:
        harmonized:
          description: Spread in absolute terms, adjusted for the cover ratio.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        relative:
          description: Spread relative to the ask price.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - harmonized
      - relative
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_delta:
      description: Delta. It represents the first partial derivative of the function
        determining the derivative notation's theoretical price with respect to the
        underlying level, evaluated at the underlying level. Delta indicates the ratio
        of the absolute change of the price of a derivative for an indefinitely small
        absolute change in the underlying level, thus it represents the price sensitivity
        of the derivative relative to changes in the underlying level. This key figure
        is calculated for plain vanilla warrants only.
      example:
        effective: 1.7325933120207193
        unadjusted: 8.28965939814297
      properties:
        effective:
          description: Delta calculated using the actual cover ration of the securitized
            derivative.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        unadjusted:
          description: Delta calculated using a (hypothetical) cover ratio of 1:1.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - effective
      - unadjusted
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_thetaOneWeek:
      description: Weekly theta. It represents the first partial derivative of the
        function determining the derivative notation's theoretical price with respect
        to the residual term, evaluated at the current residual term and multiplied
        by 7 / 365. Weekly theta indicates the absolute change (decrease) of the price
        of a derivative for a reduction of the residual term by one week (seven calendar
        days), thus it represents the price sensitivity of the derivative relative
        to changes in the residual term. This key figure is calculated for plain vanilla
        warrants only.
      example:
        effective: 6.623518433804886
        unadjusted: 4.573936264232251
      properties:
        effective:
          description: Weekly theta calculated using the actual cover ratio of the
            securitized derivative.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        unadjusted:
          description: Weekly theta calculated using a (hypothetical) cover ratio
            of 1:1.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - effective
      - unadjusted
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_vega:
      description: Vega. It represents the first partial derivative of the function
        determining the derivative notation's theoretical price with respect to the
        implied volatility, evaluated at the current implied volatility. Vega indicates
        the ratio of the absolute change of the price of a derivative for an absolute
        change of the implied volatility, thus it represents the price sensitivity
        of the derivative relative to changes in the implied volatility. This key
        figure is calculated for plain vanilla warrants only.
      example:
        effective: 8.863729185622827
        unadjusted: 9.254183946267839
      properties:
        effective:
          description: Vega calculated using the actual cover ratio of the securitized
            derivative.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        unadjusted:
          description: Vega calculated using a (hypothetical) cover ratio of 1:1.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - effective
      - unadjusted
    inline_response_200_6_keyFigures:
      description: Key figures specific to securitized derivatives; based on ask prices.
      example:
        agio:
          annualized: 5.507386964179881
          absolute: 0.5199002018724985
          relative: 7.933506881737151
        breakEven:
          distance:
            absolute: 4.459605034958679
            relative: 3.901545264248647
          breakEvenPoint: 8.251625748923757
        leverage: 1.8268702177058116
        sidewaysYield:
          annualized: 7.260521264802104
          absolute: 1.041444916118296
          relative: 4.678947989005849
        parity: 5.312489704336296
        delta:
          effective: 1.7325933120207193
          unadjusted: 8.28965939814297
        discount:
          absolute: 4.86315908102884
          relative: 6.073898085781152
        timeValue: 0.4182561061793122
        impliedVolatility: 9.183123594773994
        omega: 3.502657762086401
        spread:
          harmonized: 0.43431398824148815
          relative: 2.9409642974827896
        thetaOneWeek:
          effective: 6.623518433804886
          unadjusted: 4.573936264232251
        bonusYield:
          annualized: 4.258773108174356
          absolute: 0.2025324113236393
          relative: 6.628464275087742
        maximumYield:
          annualized: 9.702963800023566
          absolute: 9.132027271330688
          relative: 0.8774076871421566
        currency:
          isoCode: isoCode
          id: 4.078845849666752
        intrinsicValue: 8.761432466225475
        vega:
          effective: 8.863729185622827
          unadjusted: 9.254183946267839
        outperformancePoint: 5.299143560275359
      properties:
        currency:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_currency'
        bonusYield:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_bonusYield'
        sidewaysYield:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_sidewaysYield'
        maximumYield:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_maximumYield'
        agio:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_agio'
        discount:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_discount'
        breakEven:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_breakEven'
        spread:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_spread'
        delta:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_delta'
        thetaOneWeek:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_thetaOneWeek'
        vega:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_6_keyFigures_vega'
        leverage:
          description: Leverage. It represents the ratio of the underlying level to
            the ask price of the securitized derivative, adjusted for the cover ratio
            and the currency cross rate. This key figure is calculated only for leveraged
            securitized derivatives (e.g. warrants, knock-out certificates).
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        omega:
          description: Omega. It represents unadjusted delta (see attribute `delta.unadjusted`)
            multiplied with the leverage (see attribute `leverage`), both calculated
            based on the ask price of the derivative. Omega indicates the elasticity
            of the securitized derivative's price regarding the underlying level.
            This key figure is calculated for plain vanilla warrants only.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        impliedVolatility:
          description: Implied volatility. It represents the volatility of the underlying
            that justifies the ask price of the derivative, when used as a parameter
            in the derivative's pricing model (such as Black-Scholes). Its value is
            a result of the pricing process, thus it represents the annual volatility
            of the underlying expected by the market participants until maturity of
            the derivative. This key figure is calculated for plain vanilla warrants
            only.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        intrinsicValue:
          description: Intrinsic value. It represents the difference between the underlying
            level and the strike of the securitized derivative, adjusted for the cover
            ratio and the currency cross rate. If the difference is negative, the
            intrinsic value is given as 0. The intrinsic value represents the theoretical
            profit from an immediate exercise of the derivative. This key figure is
            calculated for plain vanilla warrants only.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        timeValue:
          description: Time value. It represents the difference between the ask price
            of the securitized derivative and its intrinsic value (see attribute `intrinsicValue`).
            This key figure is calculated for plain vanilla warrants only.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        outperformancePoint:
          description: Outperformance point. It represents the underlying level from
            which the underlying starts to outperform the securitized derivative,
            thus the investor would be better off investing directly in the underlying.
            It is calculated only for securitized derivatives with a limited payout
            (e.g. capped products). For the value unit, see attribute `instrument.underlying.valueUnit`.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        parity:
          description: Parity. It represents the difference between the underlying
            level and the strike of the derivative, adjusted for the cover ratio and
            the currency cross rate. Negative values are possible. It is the gain
            or loss that would result from the immediate exercise of an already present
            warrant and a simultaneously executed compensation transaction on the
            spot markets. This key figure is calculated for plain vanilla warrants
            only.
          format: real
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - currency
      - bonusYield
      - sidewaysYield
      - maximumYield
      - agio
      - discount
      - breakEven
      - spread
      - delta
      - thetaOneWeek
      - vega
      - leverage
      - omega
      - impliedVolatility
      - intrinsicValue
      - timeValue
      - outperformancePoint
      - parity
    inline_response_200_6_performance_sinceIssue:
      description: Relative performance since issue. That is the difference of a notation's
        most recent price against the price on the issue date, relative to the price
        on the issue date.
      example:
        ask: 7.606863723092579
        bid: 3.7814124730767915
      properties:
        ask:
          description: Ask-based relative performance since issue.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        bid:
          description: Bid-based relative performance since issue.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - ask
      - bid
    inline_response_200_6_performance_endOfDay:
      description: End-of-day (EOD) relative performance for different time ranges.
        The relative performance is the difference of a notation's most recent EOD
        closing price against the EOD closing price on the reference date, relative
        to the EOD closing price on the reference date.
      example:
        week1: 9.897492629215506
        month1: 5.877124706116695
        yearToDate: 8.675064425986758
        months3: 7.835035282970782
        months6: 0.4768402382624515
        years5: 3.804112695731078
        years3: 2.380090174313445
        day1: 3.111202833403195
        year1: 3.1497903714250555
      properties:
        day1:
          description: One day.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        week1:
          description: One week.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        month1:
          description: One month.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        months3:
          description: Three months.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        months6:
          description: Six months.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        year1:
          description: One year.
          format: relativeValue
          type: number
          x-sortable: true
        years3:

        fsym:

        typeComposite:
          description: Type of composite instrument, in case the underlying is a composite
            instrument.
          enum:
          - basket
          - alphaStructure
          - futuresSpread
          - factorIndex
          type: string
          x-enum-description:
          - A basket is a composite instrument which consists of several components.
            Its value is calculated as the weighted combination of the levels of the
            components. All weights are positive.
          - An alpha structure is a composite instrument which consists of two components.
            Its value is calculated as the difference of the performances of the components.
            The performances are measured starting at the date specified in the conditions
            of the securitized derivative.
          - 'A futures spread is a composite instrument which is built of two or more
            different futures contracts as its components. '
          - A factor index is a composite instrument that reflects the day-to-day
            performance of its component, multiplied with a constant factor. The related
            capital costs and fees for calculation and administration are not represented.
